@drucker-nir, the new BIKE code from #576 is failing on our continuous integration system in some AVX512f-related code; see https://circleci.com/gh/open-quantum-safe/openssl/1192 which contains error message:

```  CPPAS    additional/libkembike1_l1_cpa_la-gf_mul.lo
In file included from /usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-linux-gnu/5/include/immintrin.h:45:0,
                 from additional/secure_decode_avx512.c:35:
/usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-linux-gnu/5/include/avx512fintrin.h: In function 'OQS_KEM_bike1_l1_cpa_rotate_right':
/usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-linux-gnu/5/include/avx512fintrin.h:997:10: error: the last argument must be an 8-bit immediate
   return (__m512i) __builtin_ia32_psrlqi512_mask ((__v8di) __A, __B,
          ^
/usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-linux-gnu/5/include/avx512fintrin.h:918:10: error: the last argument must be an 8-bit immediate
   return (__m512i) __builtin_ia32_psllqi512_mask ((__v8di) __A, __B,
          ^
```

Are you able to assist?  I don't have a machine with AVX512f on it.

